Single-Qubit Common Gates Circuit: Janus vs Qiskit Performance Test

Overview

This test measured the execution time of a single-qubit gate sweep circuit run repeatedly in a loop, comparing the Janus runtime against an equivalent Qiskit implementation. The Janus file used circ, qubit, run, and print operands along with the full set of single-qubit gates available in the gates namespace. The Python file used Qiskit's AerSimulator with transpilation. Both files applied the same eleven gates (H, X, Y, Z, S, T, Sdg, Tdg, SX, SXdg, I) to a single qubit and printed the result on each iteration. The loop count (PARAM) was varied across fourteen distinct configurations. All times are from PowerShell's Measure-Command and reflect total wall-clock execution time including any runtime startup cost.

